gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Suns 123, Pelicans 109
gameRecap.excerpt: The Suns won their fourth consecutive game as they defeated the Pelicans, 123-109. Devin Booker went for a season-high 52 points (18-30 FG, 6-11 3PT), along with four rebounds, and five assists. Kevin Durant added 26 points and five rebounds. Zion Williamson led New Orleans with 24 points as Brandon Ingram added 17 points, seven rebounds, and 11 assists. The Suns move to 23-18 on the year as the Pelicans move to 25-18.
